    "description": [
        "Episode number 9 of Series \"Principles of accounting\". Demonstrates how to prepare classified financial statements for a Merchandising Business and how to analyse the statements to determine whether the firm would be a good investment. Looks at a worksheet to indicate how income statements are prepared. Briefly reviews Merchandising Accounts and the calculation of 'Net Income'. Explains 'Inventory Turnover Ratio', 'Current and Longterm Assets' and 'Liquidity'."
